<br>
They have hp so low that it would be trivial to kill the pet, but how many mellee know this? Most just assume they can ignore a pet and focus on the mage. Maybe with rage by the time that they notice they are losing hp and turn on the pet, we can turn around and nuke, or chain cast rages. Any thoughts? I'm curious what this change might do as mages are in sore need of help on the PvP servers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#333333>(3/27/02 7:44:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1 sec cast time rage pet- PvP mages new best friend?</span><hr size=1> I dont have the spell yet, but i think it would win the day against petless casters, or as a backup pet if you have to kill your regular pet(or your enemy kills it). I doubt melees will be fooled for long by this and once they find out they only have to sneeze at the pet to kill it, chaincasting wont do any good. It could be a nice tactic to alternate regular pets and rages, get rage out when your pet is feared and you bootkill it etc.<br>
Its not a killer i think, but could be a good option.<br>
